Integration test suite (Rust port of `test/editor.test.ts`) exercising the `steno` crate's editor simulation, serialization, and cursor-movement compilation end to end through its public API — no internal modules touched.

Tests hinge on a local `show(events, behaviors) -> String` helper that renders `interpret()`'s output as a buffer string with a literal `<>` marker at the cursor (`rest` index into the char vector), and on `type_text`/`key` helpers that build `Event::Text`/`Event::Key` sequences. Any change to `Event`, `Behaviors`, or `interpret`'s `EditorState` shape (specifically the `buffer` and `rest` fields) must keep this helper working or every test in the file breaks silently at the call site, not in library code.

Coverage is organized around the three exported `Behaviors` presets — `PLAIN` (literal typing, bare-newline Enter), `SMART` (auto-close/type-over of parens, no auto-indent, does not auto-close `<`), and `SMART_INDENT` (block-expand on `{` + Enter with 4-space indent, sibling Enter preserves indent level, Backspace dedents a full level). These tests double as the executable spec for indent-width (`4` spaces) and which brackets auto-close (parens but not angle brackets) — changing indent width or the auto-close set in the library requires updating expected strings here.

Serialization tests pin exact stenography-style output syntax: marks never split a surrounding text span, trailing spaces before a key get wrapped as `{^ ^}`, plain keys render as `{#KeyName}`, Enter renders as a literal `\n` and terminates/breaks any open `{#...}` group (so `Enter` between two `Up`/`End` sequences prevents them from merging into one group). Movement tests pin `movement_events(text, from, to) -> Result<Vec<Event>, RenderError>`'s behavior: same-line moves compile to repeated `Left`, cross-line moves compile to `Up`, `End`, then `Left`s, and `from == to` yields an empty vec (not an error, not a no-op event).